                    <history>
                        <origin>
                            <p>
                                <origDate notAfter="1325" notBefore="1301">14th century, first quarter</origDate>
                            </p>
                        </origin>
                        <provenance>
                            <p>Origin and early provenance unknown. The manuscript has been at the National Library since at least the 17th century. It is listed in Jaches's catalogue of 1698 (U 122) as <quote>nr 149 in fol.</quote>, and in the catalogue of 1734 (U 125e) as <quote>nr 4 theol. in fol</quote>. The spine also carries the signum <quote>e. 30. 4.</quote> from Hammarsköld’s 19th century catalogue (U 133), as well as two unidentified signa (only partially legible).</p>
                        </provenance>
                    </history>
