                        <msContents>
                            <textLang mainLang="la"/>
                            <msItem>
                                <locus from="1r" to="90v" scheme="folios"/>
                                <author>
                                    <persName ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/person/102518"> Rabanus Maurus </persName>
                                </author>
                                <title type="desc">Commentary on Maccabees, Ezra, Nehemiah and Judith</title>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">Prologue</title>
                                    <incipit>DOmino excelletissimo et in cultu christiane religionis strenuissimo lodouico regi rabanus uilissimus seruorum dei </incipit>
                                    <explicit>tempore nostri memorem conseruare dignetur</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="1r" to="42v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">On Maccabees 1-2</title>
                                    <incipit>Machabeorum libri duo prenotant prelia inter hebreorum duces</incipit>
                                    <explicit>ut in xiii die et in xiii:o mensis habite pariter jungerentur</explicit>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="43r" to="79r" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">On Ezra and Nehemiah 1-2</title>
                                    <incipit>SIcut cyrus destructo caldeorum imperio populum dei liberauit </incipit>
                                    <explicit>In altari holocaustorum cum in cordibus electorum opera iusticie flamma caritatis perficiuntur</explicit>
                                    <finalRubric>explicit esdras</finalRubric>
                                </msItem>
                                <msItem>
                                    <locus from="79v" to="90v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <title type="desc">On Judith</title>
                                    <incipit>QVeritur quo temporum quibusne regibus historia iudith</incipit>
                                    <explicit>
                                        <supplied reason="omitted">T</supplied>ransitoribus quorum unus dicebat peregrinus sum sicut omnes patres mei </explicit>
                                    <finalRubric>Explicit liber iudith</finalRubric>
                                    <note>Two leaves, <locus from="89" to="89" scheme="folios"/> and <locus from="90" to="90" scheme="folios"/>, have been placed in the wrong order. <locus from="90v" to="90v" scheme="folios"/> ends with Judith 16:2 and <locus from="89v" to="89v" scheme="folios"/> contains the end of the commentary on Judith. The explicit cited is found on <locus from="89v" to="89v" scheme="folios"/>.</note>
                                </msItem>
                                <note>The main portion of the commentary is written in a smaller script next to the main text and keyed to it by the use of lemmata. There is also a secondary layer in the margins consisiting of titles and references to authorities. This layer also seems to be part of the planned design.</note>
                                <bibl>
                                    <title type="short" ref="https://www.manuscripta.se/bibl/107168">PL</title>
                                    <citedRange from="109" to="109" unit="volume"/>
                                    <citedRange from="279" to="592" unit="column"/>
                                    <citedRange from="1125" to="1256" unit="column"/>
                                </bibl>
                            </msItem>
                        </msContents>
                        <physDesc>
                            <objectDesc>
                                <supportDesc material="parchment">
                                    <support>
                                        <p>
                                            <locus from="1r" to="90v" scheme="folios"/>
                                            <material>Parchment</material>
                                            <dimensions type="leaf">
                                                <height quantity="305" unit="mm"/>
                                                <width quantity="230" unit="mm"/>
                                            </dimensions>
                                        </p>
                                    </support>
                                    <extent>
                                        <measure type="textblockLeaves" quantity="90" unit="folios"/>
                                    </extent>
                                    <condition>The parchment is of an uneven quality and somewhat worn; it has a tear on <locus from="75" to="75" scheme="folios"/>. There are also a few repairs, e.g. on <locus from="68" to="68" scheme="folios"/>. On <locus from="39" to="39" scheme="folios"/> and <locus from="43" to="43" scheme="folios"/> small rectangular pieces have been cut out, no loss of text. <locus from="42v" to="42v" scheme="folios"/>, smudge or dirt, text still legible.</condition>
                                </supportDesc>
                                <layoutDesc>
                                    <layout>
                                        <dimensions type="written">
                                            <height quantity="225" unit="mm"/>
                                            <width quantity="140" unit="mm"/>
                                        </dimensions>
                                        <note>The text has an elborately designed layout with a main text and a commentary next to it. The written area of the main text expands or retracts in size dependig on the amount of commentary. At its largest it extends over 27 lines and all of the text surface, e.g. <locus from="16v" to="16v" scheme="folios"/>. In other cases the commentary may take up the majority of the page, e.g. <locus from="23r" to="23r" scheme="folios"/>. The commentary is written in half the size of the main text and is keyed to it with the help of lemmata. The ruling is a complex grid structure that takes into account the commentary. The ruling is made in lead or faint ink. Prickings in the margins.</note>
                                    </layout>
                                </layoutDesc>
                            </objectDesc>
                            <handDesc>
                                <handNote xml:id="hand-1">Southern textualis.</handNote>
                            </handDesc>
                            <additions>
                                <p>
                                    <locus from="1r" to="90v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    <note>Extensive marginal and interlinear glossing througout. The majority of the glosses seem to be by the scribe (or a contemporary hand) and are probably part of the planned commentary. These glosses consist of references to authorities, corrections and occasional additions. There is also a layer of extensive, but almost invisible, glossing in lead or silver point, e.g. <locus from="9" to="9" scheme="folios"/> and <locus from="15r" to="15r" scheme="folios"/>. In addition, there are scattered additions by a later medieval hand, e.g. <locus from="13v" to="13v" scheme="folios"/> and more frequently on <locus from="79r" to="90v" scheme="folios"/>.</note>
                                </p>
                                <p>
                                    <locusGrp>
                                        <locus from="43r" to="43r" scheme="folios"/>
                                        <locus from="79r" to="79r" scheme="folios"/>
                                        <locus from="79v" to="79v" scheme="folios"/>
                                    </locusGrp>
                                    <note>Titles and notes in ink by an early modern hand.</note>
                                </p>
                            </additions>
                            <decoDesc>
                                <p>Main text in brown ink. Capitals in blue or red.</p>
                                <decoNote type="initials">
                                    <p>
                                        <locus from="1r" to="1r" scheme="folios"/>: opening puzzle initial D over 8 lines in blue and red. Flourishing in same colours in counter space and around intial. The flourishing extends into the upper margin where it forms a border. Below the opening initial the following two paragraphs each contain an initial over 3 lines in blue and red with flourishing in contrasting colours. <locus from="1r" to="79v" scheme="folios"/>: Every book opens with a puzzle initial in similar style to the opening initial, with some variation in size.</p>
                                </decoNote>
                            </decoDesc>
